NAIROBI, KENYA: A mason died when a falling stone hit him in Kileleshwa area, Nairobi. Police say the worker was on the ground floor when the stone fell from the tenth floor of a building under construction along Kikambala Road. The victim died instantly and the&nbsp;police were called to pick up the body on Wednesday morning. This is the second incident to happen in the area. Another worker died in the area last week when he slid and fell from the fourth floor of a house that was under construction. Police and County officials say they are investigating to establish how and why the incidents are happening. According to officials, there is need for safety measures at such sites for the workers.